Here's how to diagnose `ReflectionTypeLoadException` with a custom `AssemblyLoadContext` on Linux:

### 1. Log the inner exceptions first

```csharp
try
{
    var types = assembly.GetTypes();
}
catch (ReflectionTypeLoadException ex)
{
    foreach (var loaderEx in ex.LoaderExceptions)
        Console.WriteLine(loaderEx);
}
```

This often reveals the exact missing or mismatched dependency immediately.

### 2. Collect an assembly-loading trace

Set these environment variables **before** launching your app:

```bash
export COREHOST_TRACE=1
export COREHOST_TRACEFILE=host_trace.log
dotnet ./YourApp.dll
```

`host_trace.log` will contain the full probing path for every assembly the host tries to resolve.

### 3. Collect a runtime event trace (more granular)

```bash
# Install if needed
dotnet tool install -g dotnet-trace

# Collect AssemblyLoader events
dotnet-trace collect \
  --providers Microsoft-Windows-DotNETRuntime:0x4:4 \
  -- dotnet ./YourApp.dll
```

Provider keyword `0x4` = **Loader** events, level `4` = Informational. Open the resulting `.nettrace` in PerfView or `dotnet-trace convert --format speedscope`.

### 4. Subscribe at runtime (in your `AssemblyLoadContext`)

```csharp
using System.Runtime.Loader;

AssemblyLoadContext.Default.Resolving += (ctx, name) =>
{
    Console.WriteLine($"[Resolving] {name} in {ctx.Name}");
    return null; // fall through to default probing
};

// Also hook your custom ALC
myPluginContext.Resolving += (ctx, name) =>
{
    Console.WriteLine($"[Plugin ALC Resolving] {name}");
    return null;
};
```

### Common root causes

| Symptom in `LoaderExceptions` | Fix |
|---|---|
| `FileNotFoundException` for a transitive dep | Publish the plugin with `dotnet publish` so deps are copied |
| Version mismatch / `FileLoadException` | Align the shared dependency version, or set `isCollectible` and isolate |
| Platform-specific native lib missing | Ship the correct `linux-x64` rid assets with the plugin |

**Start with step 1** — the `LoaderExceptions` array almost always tells you exactly which assembly or type failed and why.
